<HEADLINE> Sudan, Britain to Exchange Ambassadors Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Sudan and Britain will exchange
their accredited ambassadors in the coming few days as a result of
the detente of bilateral ties, a Sudanese official said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese-U.K. relations underwent their lowest ebb due to
Britain's siding with the United States in its air strikes on a
Sudanese medical plant last August.
</P>
<P>
The detente came following diplomatic shuttle moves that
clarified the facts about Sudan, the Sudanese News Agency quoted
Minister of State with the Foreign Ministry Archbishop Kebrial as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Kebrial also mentioned the breakthrough in the
Sudanese-Egyptian relations after the current Sudanese government
came to power.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Sudan and Egypt were extremely tense
after an abortive attempt on Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak's
life in Addis Ababa in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese officials noted that intensive efforts are being
made by the two sides to solve the problems between the two
countries. He declined to elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Among the major problems are security, the border dispute on
Halayb and the return of Egypt's properties in Sudan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
