<HEADLINE> Intensified Efforts Required for Creating Jobs in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- African countries were urged here
Tuesday to intensify their efforts for the creation of job
opportunities through mobilizing common resources in the
continent.
</P>
<P>
The Alliance for the Industrialization of Africa said in a
report to Salim Ahmed Salim, Secretary-General of the Organization
of African Unity (OAU), that the priority should be given to the
concretization of the alliance.
</P>
<P>
Heads of the 17-member alliance, who met in Algiers for a
meeting sidelined at the on-going OAU summit, said that in order
to achieve industrialization on the continent, an "African
privatization network" was set up in a bid to contribute to the
sharing and exchange of experiences and advice between the
national and local agencies in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Some African countries have set up industrial partnership
councils, with the objectives of encouraging consultations between
the private and public sectors, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The experiences which are said to be "satisfying" in Ghana,
Cote d' Ivoire and Senegal, are to be extended to a local level,
the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
