<HEADLINE> U.N. Official Satisfied With China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Didier Opertti, president
of the 53rd session of the United Nations General Assembly,
Tuesday expressed satisfaction with the results of his five-day
China visit which ended Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The president held friendly discussions "characterized by the
spirit of cooperation" with Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
high-ranking officials including Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, a
press release issued by the General Assembly said.
</P>
<P>
Discussion participants "considered different aspects of the
current international political situation," it said.
</P>
<P>
"It was agreed that efforts needed to be made to continue and
implement the reforms aimed at strengthening the role the United
Nations should play in matters relating to the maintenance of
international peace and security, as stipulated in the (U.N.)
Charter," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"In that context, both sides agreed on the need to increase the
representation of the developing countries in the Security
Council," the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Opertti, also Uruguayan foreign minister, visited China from
July 5-10. 
</P>
