<HEADLINE> OAU Summit to Enforce DRC Ceasefire Agreement: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba, the mediator of the recent ceasefire agreement on the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), said here Tuesday afternoon
that the ongoing summit of the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
will help enforce the implementation of the peace accord.
</P>
<P>
He made these remarks when addressing a small-scale press
briefing in the Sheraton Hotel.
</P>
<P>
He said the OAU would be in charge of the deployment of neutral
forces in the DRC and it would cooperate with the United Nations
and other U.N. agencies.
</P>
<P>
The ceasefire agreement, signed by regional leaders in Lusaka
on July 10 this year, was a result of tireless mediation efforts
by President Chiluba who shuttled between the countries involved
in the 11-month armed conflict.
</P>
<P>
The civil war erupted in early August of 1998 and sucked in six
other countries soon afterwards, making it a regional war in the
Great Lakes region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
