<HEADLINE> Mozambique's Economy in Rapid Recovery: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Alberro Chissano said here Tuesday afternoon that his country's
economy is in quick recovery after 16 years of war.
</P>
<P>
The president, who is attending the ongoing summit of the
Organization of African Unity here in the Algerian capital, told
Xinhua in an interview that the economy is growing at a two-digit
rate, the fastest in its history and in Africa.
</P>
<P>
"The currency is stable and we have the lowest inflation. The
environment for economic growth is becoming increasingly better,"
the president said.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted, Mozambique is still facing a lot of
difficulties in the reconstruction drive. "We have a ravaged
country because of the war," he added.
</P>
<P>
"We still have a very high percentage of poverty, but we are
not disturbed by this. What is important is how to apply efforts
to reverse this situation and now we are doing it," the president
said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment inflow into the country has been increasing
and there has been big progress in health care, power supply and
some other sectors.
</P>
<P>
The president said he was optimistic that the national economy
would enjoy further development in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
