<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Science Fiction Degree to Be Set Up in UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- A British university announced
Tuesday it will offer the country's first Bachelor of Science
degree in Science and Science Fiction from September.
</P>
<P>
The degree has been specially designed to achieve a "balance
between the study of science in its accepted format and the
phenomenon of science fiction," the University of Glamorgan said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The university, which has previously offered a course which
considered the possibility of extra-terrestrial life, said the aim
of the degree is to identify the relationship between science and
science fiction in a revolutionary new way of encouraging more
people to consider careers in science.
</P>
<P>
Students will be able to pursue particular specialisms within
the degree but will need to sustain their study of science
disciplines alongside their science-fiction related modules.
</P>
<P>
They will tackle topics such as "Will robots take over the
earth?", which can be considered from the perspectives of both
science fiction and science fact.
</P>
<P>
And the cultural significance of science and science fiction
will also be examined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
