<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Private Clinics Permitted to Conduct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian health authorities
announced Tuesday that it would provide private health
institutions with license enabling them to conduct HIV/AIDS blood
test.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health had issued a directive allowing private
clinics throughout the country to involve in undertaking blood
test for HIV, the virus that causes the lethal AIDS disease,
senior official of the ministry Assefa Wolde-Tsadiq said.
</P>
<P>
Under the latest regulations, private health institutions above
junior clinics can conduct the HIV/AIDS blood test.
</P>
<P>
It was estimated that there were 2.5 million people infected
with HIV in Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
