<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Denies Deadline for Withdrawal From Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Tuesday termed as pack
of lies the Indian propaganda that Islamabad has been given
deadline of July 16 to complete the process of disengagement in
Kargil sector in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Describing it as "boastful propaganda," Foreign Office
spokesman Tariq Altaf told media that it was absolutely wrong on
the part of India to make such a claim.
</P>
<P>
He regretted that India was saying to create an impression of
pressuring Pakistan over what has already been agreed upon.
</P>
<P>
Altaf noted that the schedule of disengagement from different
sectors along the Line of Control in Kashmir was decided by the
Director Generals of Military Operations (DGMO) of the two
countries on July 11.
</P>
<P>
It was agreed upon between the DGMO that disengagement in
Mashkoh sector would be completed in four to five days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
