<DOCNO> XIE19990714.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-13 16:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rich Oil Reserves Found in Iraq's Western Desert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Rich oil reserves and hydrocarbon
susbstance have been found in Iraq's Western Desert, said an Iraqi
oil official on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement carried by the Iraqi News Agency (INA), Ibrahim
Abdulkareem, the director-general of the Iraqi Oil Exploration
Company, said prospecting made by the Oil Ministry has shown the
country's Western Desert is rich in oil and hydrocabon substance.
</P>
<P>
Abdulkareem said his company's staff expanded activities in
searching and digging new wells in the Western Desert to find new
oil reserves. He did not reveal the estimated oil reserves in
this area.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's proven oil reserves, which stand at 112 billion barrels,
rank the second in the world only next to Saudi Arabia, whose oil
reserves are 260 billion barrels.
</P>
<P>
Iraq expects to add about 214 billion barrels to its oil
reserves, said the Iraqi official. He did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1991 Gulf War touched off by Iraq's invasion of
Kuwait, Iraq has not been allowed to sell its oil freely on
world markets under relevant U.N. resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Under the oil-for-food program which came into force in
December 1996, Iraq is allowed to export limited amount of oil in
every six months to buy food, medicine and other basic needs for
its people.
</P>
<P>
Iraq plans to increase its daily oil export capacity to 3.5
million barrels by the year 2000 from the current level of 2
million barrels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
