<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Govt Army Beats off UNITA Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The headquarters of the general
staff of Angola's armed forces announced here Tuesday that
government army beat off an unknown number of UNITA soldiers
attempting to occupy Chitembo city in central Bie Province over
the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters said in a brief statement that the forces of
the rebel National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) incurred "grave casualties" during the fighting in the
city 100 kilometers south of the capital city Kuito.
</P>
<P>
However, no details were given, except that "a UNITA political
commissioner commanding the operation" was killed.
</P>
<P>
After the victory in Chitembo, the government army went on to
chase the enemy in the direction of Camacupa city, 80 kilometers
southeast of Kuito, which is still under UNITA's control, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said UNITA's strategy now in areas with the
fiercest fightings is to try to consume the strength of government
army so as to impoverish the latter's plan of launching an
offensive in the dry season.
</P>
<P>
The army headquarters noted that despite some "individual
events of armed attacks by (Jonas) Savimbi's bandits," the present
situation in "most of the country" is still under government's
control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
