<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints New Representative in Bosnia-Herzegovina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Tuesday appointed Jacques Paul Klein as his special
representative and coordinator for United Nations Operations in
Bosnia and Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
Klein, a U.S. citizen, has served previously as the U.N.
Transitional Administrator for Eastern Slavonia, Baranja and
Western Sirmium, is presently the Principal Deputy High
Representative in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
Succeeding Elizabeth Rehn who has served as the
Secretary-General's special representative since January 1998,
Klein will assume his post on August 2, a U.N. spokesman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
