<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Parties Of China Refuting Taiwan Leader's Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Members of China's non-communist
parties today refuted the separatist remarks made recently by Lee
Teng-hui, saying the remarks reveal his intention to undermine
China's national sovereignty and territorial integrity and that
this is opposed by all the Chinese people, including Taiwan
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Tienong, the executive vice-chairman of the Chinese
Kuomintang Revolutionary Committee's Central Committee, pointed
out that there is only one China in the world and Taiwan is  part
of China and none can change this fact.
</P>
<P>
Qian Weichang, an honorary chairman of the 8th Central
Committee of the China Democratic League, said that Lee has
strayed too far on the separationist path and has risked the
future of Taiwan and its people, something that is certain to make
all the Chinese people more wary and that they will strongly
oppose it.
</P>
<P>
Wan Guoquan, the honorary vice-chairman of the 7th Central
Committee of the China Democratic National Construction
Association, said that the one-China policy is the foundation of
the cross-straits relations and that Lee's intention is to
separate Taiwan from China and make the Taiwan issue an
international one.
</P>
<P>
Xu Jialu, the chairman of the 10th Central Committee of the
China Association for Promoting Democracy, pointed out that Lee's
remarks have posed a great threat to the cross-straits relations
which are developing smoothly in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
