<DOCNO> XIE19990714.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bus Carrying 8 Passengers Hijacked in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- An Albanian man on Wednesday
hijacked an inter-city bus carrying eight passengers on its way
from Polykastro to Thessaloniki in northern Greece.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old hijacker, identified as Aleksandr Nana and
armed with six hand grenades, asked for about 793,650 U.S. dollars
and two weapons in return for releasing the hostages, the semi-
official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
However, later reports said that Nana, whose face is covered
with a ski-mask, would cross into Albania alone at the
Krystallopigi border post after releasing the hostages unharmed.
</P>
