<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Freezes Work Permits to Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus announced Wednesday to
suspend issuance of new working permits to foreign workers until
September 30.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a cabinet meeting, Interior Minister
Christodoulos Christodoulou said the cabinet adopted a suggestion
put forward by a ministerial commission made up of Christodoulou,
Justice Minister Nicos Koshis and Labor Minister Andreas
Moushouttas.
</P>
<P>
Christodoulou said further details would be revealed by the
labor minister within the next few days.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out, however, that exceptions will be made for
certain groups of workers such as domestic helpers and seasonal
workers, and that permits for replacement of workers will be
examined.
</P>
<P>
Trade unions of the country consistently accuse foreign
workers, legal and illegal, of "stealing" job opportunities from
local people.
</P>
<P>
There are some 15,000 foreigners working on the island legally,
and another estimated 10,000 working illegally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
