<HEADLINE> French Mountaineer Dies in Western Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- French mountaineer Lahor Pascal had
lost his life Tuesday evening when he ascended a peak overlooking
Khorramabad, the capital of Iran's western province of Lorestan,
the Islamic Republic News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pascal traveled with a group of French mountaineers upon an
invitation from Iran's Mountaineering Federation to carry out
research studies on Iranian heights and mountains, said Baqer
Kashfi, Director General of the Physical Training Organization in
Lorestan.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted Kashfi as saying that the accident
occurred when Pascal was examining a new route on a cliff.
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old French mountaineer had nailed 65 meters of the
150-meter-high cliff when he fell down on his way back due to
failure of one of the nails, Kashfi said.
</P>
<P>
The French mountaineers had already examined other routes on
some Iranian mountains before traveling to Lorestan, the official
added. 
</P>
