earnings due to sharp price cuts on its chips, but said sales and
profit margins for the rest of the year would be strong. The chip
maker's net income rose 49 percent to 1.75 billion dollars. The
result reflect a fierce effort to take back market share in the
sales of chips for low-cost computers.
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. House Republicans unveiled a 10-year 863.9 bilion
dollars tax package, despite the likelihood of a presidential veto.
</P>
</TEXT>
