<HEADLINE> OAU Summit Ends With Declaration for Peace, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The 35th summit of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) ended here Wednesday morning
with a declaration urging for peace and stability in Africa and
better preparedness to face pending challenges.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said that peace and development is the
daunting challenge the continent faces at the turn of the century.
Peace is the precondition to economic recovery and development, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The summit has drawn 46 heads of state who showed, more than
ever, the courage to embrace the next millennium and expressed the
hope to do more practical work for the improvement of African
societies.
</P>
<P>
The summit has also decided that the next summit is to be held
in Togo. 
</P>
