<HEADLINE> Nikkei Ends at Year's High in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose in Tokyo Wednesday,
led mainly by high-priced blue chips, with the key Nikkei index
ending at its highest point for the year.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange surged 176.77 points, or 0.97
percent, from Tuesday to end at 18,357.86, breaking the previous
highest closing of 18,274.18 registered Monday.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 13.38 points or 0.90 percent to 1,
497.07. The TOPIX index briefly topped 1,500.00 for the first time
in almost two years.
</P>
<P>
Technology issues, several of which hit their record highs,
played the major role to lift the key market gauge, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section ballooned to 765.90 million
shares from 681.11 million shares Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were higher in most business sectors, with the
electric machinery sector standing out as the best performer,
rising 3.78.
</P>
<P>
Blue-chip issues in the sector attracted active purchases
throughout the day, with the top five most heavily traded issues
coming from the sector.
</P>
<P>
Matsushita Electric Industrial was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers narrowly
exceeded winners 610 to 584 despite the overall gain, with 134
issues ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
