<HEADLINE> Canada Not to Sell Fusion Reactor to Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Canada has agreed to drop its plan
to sell its only nuclear fusion reactor and related technology to
Iran, which the United States takes as anti-American.
</P>
<P>
The "National Post" newspaper of Canada said Wednesday that
Washington had contacted the Canadian Foreign Ministry and
received "strong assurances that Canada will block the proposed
sale."
</P>
<P>
The U.S. is concerned that Iran has become expert at procuring
industrial production technologies in order to build weapons of
mass destruction, according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. may agree that Canada sells the fusion technology to
responsible nations, the newspaper indicated.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. objection came after Washington learned last week that
Canada was negotiating with Iran on the sale as the Tokamak
reactor had lost financial support from the federal government of
Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
