<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Making Headway In Overseas Oil Market (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- An oilfield, a long oil pipeline
and an oil refinery China built in Sudan has gone into operation,
a major breakthrough in China's overseas oil work.
</P>
<P>
China National Petroleum Corp (CNPC) beat out other
international bidders on the project, which was built by its
subsidiary China Petroleum Engineering Construction Corp. (CPECC).
</P>
<P>
After more than a year of work, China finished the Muglad
Oilfield project. It has an annual production capacity of from 7.5
million tons to 10 million tons. It also involved building a 1,506-
km pipeline from Heglid in southern Sudan to the port of Sudan,
and an oil refinery that processes at least 2.5 million tons
annually.
</P>
<P>
This is China's largest overseas oil project ever that meets
international standards, according to CPECC's president Qin Anmin.
</P>
<P>
According to CNPC, China is actively exploring international
oil markets, while developing its own oil and gas resources with
foreign partners.
</P>
<P>
China plans to have a 10-million-ton-oil supply from overseas
a year by 2000 and 50 million tons of oil and 50 billion cubic
meters of gas by 2010.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990714.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Making Headway In Overseas Oil Market  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to Qin, China has made progress in these oil and gas
projects overseas and CPECC has signed overseas oil construction
contracts worth more than a billion U.S. dollars. It has also been
listed among the world's top 225 contractors for 5 consecutive
years.
</P>
<P>
Qin says that China is rich in oil resources and produces over
150 million tons of crude annually and has proven oil reserves of
17 billion tons, putting it in the 5th and 9th place respectively
in the world.
</P>
<P>
He explains that China's petroleum development strategy is to
rely mainly on domestic resources and to increase Sino-foreign
cooperation in its offshore and western oil and gas resources and
to increase entry into international oil markets. 
</P>
