<HEADLINE> India's Industrial Production Grows 7.2 Pct in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The growth rate of India's
industrial production nearly doubled to 7.2 percent in May
compared with 3.7 percent in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Statistical Organization, the sharp
increase was mainly brought about by a strong performance of the
manufacturing sector, accounting for around 80 percent of the
index of industrial production.
</P>
<P>
The sector saw a growth of 8.4 percent in May from 3.4 percent
recorded in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The cumulative growth rate for April and May, the first two
months of the current fiscal year, stood at 6.3 percent, up from
4.2 percent in the same period last year. 
</P>
