<HEADLINE> Nigerian Students Storm Police Station, Seizing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Students of Obafemi Awolowo
University in the southwestern state of Osun Tuesday stormed the
State Police Headquarters in the state's capital Osogbo and
forcefully took away one of the cult suspects in police custody.
</P>
<P>
The students who arrived at the headquarters in four buses
claimed that they handed the suspect, Efosa Idahosa to the police
so that his confessions could be recorded by security agents and
"then from here take him to Lagos to go and face the world."
</P>
<P>
Although they were persuaded by police that Efosa's being with
them would help in their investigation to unravel the
circumstances that led to the killing of eight students, the
students insisted that "Efosa must be released to us."
</P>
<P>
Even though there were some handful of policemen around, they
did not resist the irate students who later burst into songs.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian newspaper Wednesday quoted a student as explaining
why they took laws into their hands.
</P>
<P>
"We brought Efosa here by ourselves and we want to go with him.
We are not taking him away to kill him but to make him confess his
sins," said the student.
</P>
<P>
"In March this year, when seven secret cult members were
apprehended, we handed them over to the police but they claimed
that they did not have any evidence to prosecute them. The boys
were released, now, see the result, they in turn killed about
eight of us. " he added.
</P>
<P>
Five students of Nigeria's Obafemi Awolowo University including
the secretary-general of the Student Union were murdered last
Saturday following an attack on them by above 200 secret cultists.
 Three students injured in the accident died latter in a hospital.
</P>
<P>
The cultists in black carried out the bloody attack may still
poses a threat to other students at the Obafemi Awolowo Teaching
Hospital complex where the bodies of the victims have been
deposited, warned Lanre Adeleke, president of the Student Union
who narrowly escaped death.
</P>
<P>
The late secretary-general of the Student Union was shot on the
head together with his friend, while sleeping in their rooms
around 4:30 local time Saturday and his body was taken to the
corridor by the cultists.
</P>
<P>
Some students reported secret drum sound around midnight and
teamed out to search before the attack took place.
</P>
<P>
The students, according to the report, was very angry at the
authorities' silence at the accident and vowed to wage a war
against the cultists on their campus and beyond. 
</P>
</TEXT>
