<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Internet Users Hit Four Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The number of Chinese Internet
users hit 4 million last month, according to a report from the
China Internet Network Information Center (CINIC) which was made
available today.
</P>
<P>
The number of on-line computers totaled 1.46 million, with 29,
045 registered domain names, while Internet users are now surfing
through 9,906 international websites, the report says.
</P>
<P>
The report was compiled using the answers received on 52,549
questionnaires, and was accomplished in accordance with
international practice.
</P>
<P>
A considerable proportion of Internet surfers are young people
with good education living in China's economically developed
cities, according to the CINIC.
</P>
<P>
The report says that 85 percent of all users are male, and 40
percent are in the 21-25 age group. Some 86 percent have college
degrees, and computer specialists account for 25 percent of all
professional users.
</P>
<P>
China's Internet technology has developed remarkably in the
past five years and experts predict that the number of Internet
users in China will reach 5-8 million by the end of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
