<HEADLINE> More Than 50 percent of Annual Afforestation Plan Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- In the first half of this year
China stepped up its nationwide afforestation project, with more
than half of the annual target already achieved.
</P>
<P>
By May 20, the country had afforested 2.835 million hectares of
land, accounting for 59.4 percent of the annual plan, according to
statistics released today by the State Forestry Administration (
SFA).
</P>
<P>
There are now 3.267 million hectares of mountain areas closed
for afforestation, accounting for more than 50 percent of the
annual goal.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, eight provinces and autonomous regions
including Zhejiang, Anhui, Fujian, Jiangxi, Hunan, Hubei, Guangxi
and Xinjiang have completed their afforestation plan for the whole
year.
</P>
<P>
A SFA official said that governments at all levels have given
priority to afforestation and ecological protection following last
summer's flooding of the Yangtze River and the Songhua and
Nenjiang rivers.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have also issued a series of preferential
policies for afforestation, ensuring the smooth enactment of this
year's plan, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
