<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Slightly Higher in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices closed slightly
higher on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as earlier gains was
followed by profit-taking selling.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) closed at 2,178.63
points, rising by 0.14 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume decreased 485.01 million shares worth 629.51 million
Singapore dollars (370.30 million U.S. dollars). Gainers led
losers by 226 to 101 with 18 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AFP led the volume list with a turnover of 29.47 million
shares. It was followed by Hotung that had 28.38 million units
done. GoldenAg was the next with 22.88 million counters traded.
</P>
<P>
SPH again led the gainers with a gain of 130 cents to close at
33.00 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 also remained in its second
ranking by rising 90 cents to finish at 32.60 Singapore dollars.
Venture went up 40 cents to end at 14.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Thai Pr topped the descent of the day losing
50 cents to close at 5.80 U.S. dollars. SIA F shed 40 cents to
finish at 15.70 Singapore dollars. PacCent retreated 35 cents to
end at 5.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the market began the day up amid selective
buying in low-volume trading, but lost the much of the gain in
late trading.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the growing tension between China's mainland
and Taiwan after Lee Teng-hui's speech that Taiwan is
reconsidering its 'one-China' policy, had dampened the market
sentiment. 
</P>
