<HEADLINE> Philippine Government Creates Disaster-operation Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) - The Philippine Department of Social
Welfare and Development (DSWD) has organized a team to render and
sustain 24-hour disaster operation, especially in areas that may
be hit by the Mayon volcano eruption.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Vice President Gloria Arroyo, also Secretary of the
DSWT, said Wednesday that the team is composed of action officers,
information team, report and data management team, monitoring
team, reinforcement team and general administrative support teams.
</P>
<P>
The department has trained its officers in the provincial, city
and municipal Social Welfare and Development Offices and other
social workers and volunteers in the local government units in
line with the operation, Arroyo said.
</P>
<P>
Among the subjects that were tackled were disaster management,
relief operation and management of evacuation centers.
</P>
<P>
Arroyo assured that the department is already prepared for the
people who will be affected by the volcano's eruption.
</P>
<P>
Ready-to-eat food and other relief items have been made
available any time at the department's regional office, while
relief support may also be provided by its central office.
</P>
<P>
There will be no problem in the supply of rice because the
National Food Authority has agreed to allow the department to
withdraw sacks of rice from its warehouse which will then be
distributed to people the affected areas, Arroyo added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
