<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CNPC Pumps Over 53 Million Tons of Crude in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The China National Petroleum Corp.
(CNPC), the country's oil giant, turned out 53.36 million tons of
crude oil and 8 billion cu m of gas in the first half of this year,
representing increases of 35 tons and 780 million cu m,
respectively, over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The CNPC witnessed better economic performance by giving
priority to optimizing the oil product mix and cutting production
costs in the fist half of this year, enabling it to obtaining
sales income and profits totaling 164.3 billion yuan and 4.08
billion yuan, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Various enterprises under the CNPC have tried many means to
turn losses into profits, with the number of profitable
enterprises increasing by 13 percent in the first half year.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some five large money-losing enterprises under the
CNPC such as Daqing Petrochemicals and the Jilin Petrochemical
Group have reduced losses by more than 2.4 billion yuan in the
same period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
