<HEADLINE> URGENT: 15 Killed in Bus Accident in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were killed and 8
others injured on Tuesday when a bus carrying more than 20
passengers suddenly ran off the highway and fell 100 meters into a
valley near the city of Nanchong in Sichuan Province, southwest
China.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here today, survivors of the
accident said that at about 11:00 am on Tuesday, the bus, which
was on en route to Nanchong, suddenly drove off the highway and
rolled down the 100-meter deep valley. Some of the passengers were
thrown out of the bus.
</P>
<P>
The injured passengers have been taken to a local hospital for
treatment, and the cause of the accident is still under
investigation, reports said. 
</P>
