<HEADLINE> Filaria Disease Affect 59 Filipinos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-nine persons were found
infected with filariasis in the northern part of the Philippines
recently, the Philippine News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Results of blood tests conducted by the local health
surveillance team in the city of Baikingon, Cagayan Province,
showed that 42 out of the 59 infected residents are males and 17
are females.
</P>
<P>
Team leader Dr. Joey Retuya noted that the figure comprises
only 4.3 percent of the 1,362 Baikingon residents who received the
examination.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the Malaria Control Service of the
Department of Health-10 (DOH-10) recently held an entomological
survey to check the presence of mosquitoes which are possible
carriers of microfilaria.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that filariasis-carrying mosquitoes are
present in Baikingon.
</P>
<P>
In view of this, the local health authority has urged the
residents to destroy all possible breeding places of mosquitoes in
order to prevent the occurrence of filariasis and dengue in their
area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
