<DOCNO> XIE19990714.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt Assists Over 1 Million Job Seekers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) - More than a million job seekers have
been assisted by the Philippine government in the past year, the
Philippine News Agency (PNA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This record was lauded in a one-year performance report as an
achievement made as President Joseph Estrada moored employment
facilitation to his overall strategy to eradicate poverty.
</P>
<P>
Since July last year, the government has extended assistance to
457,372 local job applicants through the Department of Labor and
Employment (DOLE) and its network of 1,805 Public Employment
Service Offices (PESOs) nationwide, the PNA said.
</P>
<P>
The labor marketing efforts of the DOLE also led to the
deployment of 606,222 overseas Filipino workers to 182
international destinations during the July 1998 - March 1999
period.
</P>
<P>
According to the DOLE, of the 457,372 applicants registered
under the Estrada presidency, 353,398 were listed under the PESOs
and 93,974 more under the DOLE regional offices.
</P>
<P>
The DOLE said 226,477 job seekers were counseled on acquiring
employability, while 381,304 applicants were referred for wage
employment, self-employment and training opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Of these government-assisted applicants, the DOLE said, "a
total of 296,733 job seekers or 64.9 percent received placement
assistance."
</P>
<P>
The DOLE said its employment-facilitation services include
special programs for vulnerable sectors like the youth and persons
with disabilities.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate the matching of job seekers with available job
vacancies, the DOLE has also sponsored job fairs where job seekers
directly apply to companies participating in these special
projects.
</P>
<P>
Since July last year, the DOLE conducted 222 job fairs
nationwide that led to the hiring of 10,330 applicants by
participating companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
