<HEADLINE> Jakarta Stock Exchange Ready for New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX)
is ready to anticipate the new millennium by preparing various
facilities and infrastructures aimed at smooth, efficient, liquid
and secure stock trading activities, its President-Director Mas
Ahmad Daniri said.
</P>
<P>
In anticipation of the new millennium, Daniri said, the JSX's
big challenges are to materialize efforts to make local investors
as market leaders, to enhance the climate of openness and to
exercise good governance in the stock market.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there should also be scripless trading and remote
trading that will support market development.
</P>
<P>
"Many things have been done and many challenges have also been
passed, marked by a fluctuating composite share price index,
increasing market capitalization and increasing transactions
through the capital market," the Antara News Agency Wednesday
quoted Daniri as saying.
</P>
<P>
JSX is one of the country's biggest stock markets. During the
year of 1998, the JSX's composite share price index strengthened
by 66.6 percent to 693 points from 398 points of the previous
year. Market capitalization also increased by 164.6 percent from
176 trillion rupiah (25.13 billion U.S. dollars) in 1997 to 465
trillion rupiah (66.4 billion dollars) in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The JSX's composite share price index hovered around 660 points
recently.
</P>
<P>
According to Daniri, the average stock trading volume increased
to 512 billion rupiah (731.12 million dollars) per day last year,
while in 1997 it was only recorded at 404 billion rupiah (576.89
million dollars) per day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
