<HEADLINE> Nepali King Leaves for London for Medical Checkup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra left here
Wednesday for a regular medical checkup in London.
</P>
<P>
He was struck by cardiac ischaemia in November last year and
had a successful stent implantation that month at Cromwell
hospital in London.
</P>
<P>
Queen Aishwarya is accompanying the king on the two-week visit.
</P>
<P>
They were seen off at the airport by Crown Prince Dipendra,
Prime Minister Krishna Prasad Bhattarai and other senior
government officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
