<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index was four points lower at 2,170 with a huge
turnover of 375 million New Zealand dollars (200 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Carter Holt Harvey lost 12 cents to
236 cents, Telecom 8 to 785 cents, Contact Energy two to 306
cents, and Air New Zealand-A one cent to 305 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Stocks received a thumbs-up from investors with Energy
rising 40 cents to 610 cents, Paper 14 to 165 cents, Building four
to 300 cents and Forests one cent to 113 cents.
</P>
<P>
Telstra and Natural Gas Corp closed unchanged at 1,100 and 200
cents respectively. 
</P>
