<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay Beats Chile to Enter Copa America Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Chile blew two penalty kicks,
one in regulation time and another in the tiebreaker, and Uruguay
advanced to the final of the Copa America soccer tournament with a
5-3 victory in the penalty-kick shootout after a 1-1 tie in
Asuncion, Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
The victory was virtually a repeat of Uruguay's win over host
Paraguay in the quarter-finals by an identical 1-1 score, with
Carini again the hero with a save in the tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay, which brought a junior team to the Copa America, faces
the winner of the Brazil-Mexico matchup in the final.
</P>
<P>
Chile started stronger, with Jose Luis Sierra and Fabian Estay
controlling the midfield and veteran strikers Marcelo Salas and
Ivan Zamorano keeping Uruguay penned in its own end. But Chile
was unable to penetrate the solid defense and Uruguay gathered
courage and began to counterattack dangerously.
</P>
<P>
It was Uruguay that got a good opportunity on a corner kick in
the 22nd minute. Walter Coelho fired the ball to the far post and
Alejandro Lembo caught the defense flatfooted to head it in.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes later, Chile missed two excellent chances to tie.
</P>
<P>
Chile's pressure finally paid off in the 63th minute, when
Zamorano soared over the Uruguayan defense to head in a cross from
Sierra. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
