<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Further Strengthen Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine is to further strengthen its
military during the second phase (1999 to 2000) of its three-
phased 1997-2005 development plan by optimizing its strength,
enhancing its combat effectiveness and modernizing its equipment,
Defense Minister Alexander Kuzmuk said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this, a new structure must be established, Kuzmuk
said at the annual meeting of military officers here.
</P>
<P>
He told the meeting that seven new types of weapons had
recently been delivered to the military, including the "Snow
Leopard" automatic guided warheads, out of 11 improved weapon
systems developed in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He added the number of military personnel will be reduced from
320,000 to 310,000 and nonmilitary personnel from 100,000 to 90,
000 by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma attended the meeting which
was participated by some 500 representatives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
