<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Ancient Capitals' Folk Art Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital city of
Beijing is to host an ancient capitals' folk art festival from
August 6 to September 5.
</P>
<P>
In China's long history, seven cities served as capitals in
different dynasties and therefore have colorful folk arts. The
cities are Anyang, Luoyang and Kaifeng in central China's Henan
Province; Xi'an in northwestern China's Shaanxi Province; Nanjing
and Hangzhou of the eastern provinces of Jiangsu and Zhejiang; and
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Song and dance troupes from the seven cities will put on
performances in the Badaling section of the Great Wall other
scenic spots in Yanqing County in northwestern Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, dragon dance, lantern show, painting and calligraphy
exhibitions, arts and crafts shows, as well as a symposium on folk
custom and tourism industry, will also be held during the festival.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990714.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Adheres to One-China Policy: Rubin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. State Department on
Tuesday reiterated Washington's position to follow the one-China
policy and voiced concern about the situation arising from Lee
Teng-hui's latest separatist remarks on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"We do not support Taiwan independence. We do not support
Taiwanese membership in organizations where statehood is required.
We do not support a two-China policy or a one-China, one-Taiwan
policy," State Department spokesman James Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Lee said on July 9 that cross-straits relations should be "
state-to-state" or at least "special state-to-state."
</P>
<P>
"We have a one-China policy. That has been our policy for some
time now," Rubin affirmed.
</P>
<P>
"Our position on Taiwan's future is clear and unchanging. We
believe that it is a matter for the Chinese people on both sides
of the Taiwan Strait to resolve," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have for some time encouraged both sides to engage in
meaningful, substantive dialogue."
</P>
<P>
He said Washington would seek further information on Taipei's
position. "Let me say we will be discussing the recent statements"
made by Lee.
</P>
<P>
"We are first trying to clarify, from Taipei, what the
significance, if any, of these statements is." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
