<DOCNO> XIE19990714.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Morauta Sworn In as New PNG PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 14 (Xinhua) - Mekere Morauta was sworn
in as prime minister of Papua New Guinea (PNA) on Wednesday after
being elected by the country's parliament, AAP said.
</P>
<P>
Morauta, leader of the People's Democratic Movement, was sworn
in by PNG Governor-General Sir Silas Atopare at the Government
House, AAP said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, PNG Parliamentary Speaker Iairo Lasaro announced
Morauta had won the vote for the job by 99 to 5. The only other
nominee was East New Britain Governor Francis Koimanrea, AAP said.
</P>
<P>
Morauta becomes the sixth man to lead PNG since it gained
independence in 1975.
</P>
<P>
The country's former parliamentary speaker John Pundari had
been tipped to become prime minister after being nominated by
outgoing prime minister Bill Skate on Tuesday, but he refused to
accept the nomination on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Pundari nominated Morauta for the job.
</P>
<P>
"I accept the nomination with great pleasure," Morauta said.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later the parliamentarians divided to vote and all but
five crossed the floor to Morauta's side.
</P>
<P>
Those who crossed the floor included Skate and Fisheries
Minister Chris Haiveta, who had earlier nominated Pundari.
</P>
<P>
Skate resigned as prime minister last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
