<HEADLINE> Trade Surges in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Total trade volume in East China's
Anhui province surged 10 percent to hit 1.12 billion U.S. dollars
during the first half of 1999, with imports seeing a remarkable
jump.
</P>
<P>
The landlocked province's imports rose a year-on-year 39
percent to reach 440 million dollars while exports went down three
percent to 680 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports to the U.S. grew by 16 percent during the first half of
the year, while exports to Japan rose six percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises saw positive growth in both imports
and exports during the first half of the year and reported a year-
on-year 29 percent rise in foreign trade to 350 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports by local state-run enterprises rose 29 percent to 200
million dollars, while their exports dropped five percent to 550
million dollars. 
</P>
