<HEADLINE> Tibetan Dance "Qomolangma" Welcomed in Kunming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 Chinese and
overseas tourists have watched with great interest the Tibetan
dance entitled "Qomolangma" put on stage in the last three days in
Kunming, host city of the '99 Kunming World Horticulture
Exposition.
</P>
<P>
The 100-minute performance, which was accompanied by Tibetan
religious music and traditional instruments, was performed by
about 200 Tibetan artists. It highlights the history, culture and
religion of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The performance was sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of
Culture and the Tibetan Autonomous Regional People's Government
for marking the 50th anniversary of the founding of New China as
well as the 40th anniversary of the democratic reform in Tibet,
according to Nyima Cering, vice chairman of the autonomous
regional government.
</P>
<P>
The aim of putting the dance on stage during the '99 Kunming
World Horticulture Exposition, which runs from May 1 to October 31,
is to let more domestic and overseas tourists get access to
Tibetan culture, Nyima Cering said. The exposition is expected to
attract 10 million visitors to the capital city of southwest China
's Yunnan Province before closing.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that the Tibetan dancers will perform in other
parts of the world during a global tour later this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
