<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Armory Destroyed by Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- An accidental fire at Sri Lanka's
Welikanda Brigade headquarters in Northern province Tuesday spread
to an underground armory, destroying it and causing almost 200
massive explosions, reports reaching here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Military spokesman Sunil Tennakoon confirmed the blasts, and
said the fire was not rebel-related but an accident, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
As the shells in the armory started exploding, hundreds of
people in the neighborhood fled their homes, and schools were
temporarily closed. However, there were no casualties either among
civilians or armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The exploded ammunition included 85 mm artillery, 120 mm
mortars and 130 mm artillery. The losses are expected to run into
millions of rupees.
</P>
<P>
Troops had to temporarily move out of the brigade, the reports
added.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened a day after Tamil rebels attacked Welioya
in the region, during which at least 11 soldiers were killed.
</P>
</TEXT>
