<HEADLINE> Guatemala Seizes Seven Tons of Cocaine in Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Guatemalan authorities
seized seven tons of cocaine in the firs half of this year,
reports reaching here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Anti-narcotic Operation Department also confiscated 10
kilograms of heroin and one kilogram of crack and has so far
destroyed 398,306 marihuana plants and 20,950 poppy plants.
</P>
<P>
The department, under the National Civil Police, arrested 276
drug trafficking suspects, including Guatemalans, Salvadorans,
Colombians and Mexicans, during the six-month period.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala, which seized a total of nine tons of cocaine last
year, has seen a rise in drug trafficking through its territory
because of its strategic position, the reports said. 
