<HEADLINE> Shanghai Exchange Sees Growth in Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 12 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE)
reported a year-on-year rise of 14.06 percent in turnover to 1.89
trillion yuan in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
This was partly because of the bullish market that began on May
19 in both Shanghai and Shenzhen, bringing capitalization at the
SSE to 1.65 trillion yuan by June 31.
</P>
<P>
In the January-June period, 876.5 billion yuan worth of A
shares for domestic investors changed hands and 7.6 billion yuan
in B shares, which are reserved for overseas investors. Turnover
in investment funds amounted to 73 billion yuan, treasury bonds
topped 932 billion yuan, and other bonds surpassed 2.6 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The SSE composite stock index opened at 1144.89 points at the
beginning of the year and closed at 1689.43 points at the end of
June, with the half-year lowest being 1047.83 points on May 17 and
the highest, 1756.18 points on June 30, which was a record high.
</P>
<P>
In the six-month period, Lekai Film was the largest gainer
among A shares, with a rise of 147 percent, and among B shares it
was Mozhihua.
</P>
<P>
There were 20 A shares and two B shares listed on the SSE in
the first half. The former added nearly 14.23 billion yuan and the
latter, 39.8 million U.S. dollars. The amount of money raised by
the three investment funds was seven billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shenyin-Wanguo Securities Company led local securities
companies with 91.9 billion yuan in turnover during the first half.
</P>
</TEXT>
