<HEADLINE> Farmland in Central China Affected By Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Some 107,300 hectares of autumn
crops in central China's Henan Province, have been affected by
floods as a result of heavy rains in the past days.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the rainfalls, most of the province was hit by one of
the worst drought in history.
</P>
<P>
About 64 counties reported rainfall of 100 m.m. between July 3
and 9, with 12 counties witnessing rainfall of above 200 m.m.
</P>
<P>
In Nanzhao County, one of the seriously affected areas, 3,160
hectares of farmland has been affected and economic losses are
estimated at 12.5 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural departments at all levels in the province have
mobilized farmers to try to reduce economic losses to the minimum
level by planting new crops. 
</P>
