<HEADLINE> Six Dead, Thousands Stranded After Downpours in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Six people have died and
thousands have been stranded or evacuated as torrential rains
entered the fifth day on Tuesday in Hungary. Daily life and
agricultural production in many parts of the country are seriously
affected.
</P>
<P>
Heavy downpours which began last weekend have flooded 106 towns
and villages, affecting nearly 2,000 homes. More than 7,000 people
have been stranded by rising waters and about 1,700 people have
been evacuated to safer areas.
</P>
<P>
The record-high rainfall is expected to cause heavy damage to
agricultural production, particularly the summer harvest. Experts
estimate that heavy rains will affect wheat, the main summer crop,
both in quantity and quality.
</P>
<P>
Neighboring countries are also suffering bad weather conditions.
A rainstorm hitting Romania on Monday caused a serious landslide,
killing 15 people. 
