<HEADLINE> CONCACAF Champions Cup to Be Held in Las Vegas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The CONCACAF Champions Cup
finals will be held on September 28 to October 3 in Las Vegas, the
confederation announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion D.C. United of the United States along with
the U.S. Major League Soccer champion Chicago Fire already have
qualified for the finals along with Mexico's Toluca and Trinidad
and Tobago's Joe Public.
</P>
<P>
Three more Central American clubs will be added along with the
winner of a playoff between Mexico's Necaxa and the Los Angeles
Galaxy of MLS.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the Champions Cup qualifies for the inaugural
FIFA World Club Championship in Brazil on Jan. 5-14. 
