<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0045 GMT, July 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS -- Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika, who is
newly-appointed the head of the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
, spelt out here Tuesday the principal factors for the
reinforcement of the industrial strategies in Africa.
</P>
<P>
In a message to the sponsorship groups for the Alliance of
African Industrialization, Bouteflika said Africa is characterized
by its "weak manufacturing items in comparison with the world
production," because of the stagnation of its industrializing
process and the absence of adequate industrial strategies of the
adjusting structural programs. (OAU-Africa-Industrialization)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is
planning to visit the Middle East early in August following
President Bill Clinton's meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak in an effort to help push forward the peace process, the
State Department said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
She is expected to stop in Damascus for talks with Syrian
President Hafez Assad, meet in Jerusalem with Barak and Foreign
Minister David Levy, and with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat in
Palestinian-held territory as well as other Arab leaders. (US-
Mideast-Albright)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan Tuesday
called on the international community to help the United Nations
Interim Administration in Kosovo (UNMIK) to meet what he described
"unprecedented challenges" in the post-war reconstruction drive in
the Serbian province. (Annan-Kosovo-Reconstruction)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Negotiations between Britain and Argentina on how to
resume air links between the disputed Falkland Islands and the
Argentine mainland are expected to reach agreement on Wednesday,
British Foreign Office said.
</P>
<P>
The talks, in their third round in London now, are due to
continue on Wednesday morning and a statement is expected to be
issued around noon, a spokeswoman in the Foreign Office told
Xinhua on Tuesday.  (UK-Argentina-Falkland)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Tuesday
appointed Jacques Paul Klein as his special representative and
coordinator for United Nations Operations in Bosnia and
Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
Klein, a U.S. citizen, has served previously as the U.N.
Transitional Administrator for Eastern Slavonia, Baranja and
Western Sirmium, is presently the Principal Deputy High
Representative in Bosnia and Herzegovina. (UN-Bosnia-Herzegovina)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Amendments designed by the Protestant Ulster Unionist
Party to save the Northern Ireland peace process were rejected by
the government in Britain's House of Commons on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The amendments to the Northern Ireland Bill, want guarantees
that Sinn Fein will be excluded from a proposed Northern Ireland
government if their military wing, the Irish republic Army (IRA)
do not hand in their weapons. (Britain-Parliament-N.Ireland)
</P>
