<HEADLINE> Argentine Stock Rebounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange rebounded Tuesday by 4.59 percent
after Monday's slumping of 8.66 percent, closing at 474.71 points
against 453.86 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 42.212 million dollars against 41.537 million
dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Mervel index plunged 7.8 percent on Monday to a
three-month low, due to the rumors of government's default of
foreign debt.
</P>
<P>
Argentine government debt reached 130 billion dollars, equal to
53 percent of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest was 6.05 percent in the
24-hour term, compared with 5.95 percent on Monday. The peso
parity aginst the dollar remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase
and 1.002 for sale. 
</P>
