<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ferrari Says Schumacher's Crash Due to Loose Screw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, 13 July (Xinhua) -- Italy's Ferrari F1 team said Tuesday
that a loose screw was to blame for sending Michael Schumacher off
the track at the Britain's Silverstone Grand Prix race.
</P>
<P>
The official cause of the accident was "an unexpected loss of
pressure on the brakes' posterior circuit which was caused by the
loosening of a screw," Ferrari declared in a statement.
</P>
<P>
It said the reason for the technical mishap was not known, but
that the screw had been checked the evening before the race and
there had been no reason to carry out any further tests.
</P>
<P>
"Data shows there weren't any problems with it during the warm-
up session or during the race, until the anomalous braking,"
Ferrari said, referring to the point when Schumacher slowed down
to turn round a curve before veering off the track.
</P>
<P>
The team, which has its headquarters in the northern Italian
town of Maranello near Modena, said it was carrying out "a full
and detailed investigation" into the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
